WEBVTT

00:07.007 --> 00:09.259
[mysterious music plays]

00:16.975 --> 00:19.227
[Nami breathing shakily]

00:28.319 --> 00:29.612
[whimpering]

00:33.491 --> 00:34.701
[Nami screams]

00:35.285 --> 00:36.578
[screams]

00:37.078 --> 00:37.912
[screams]

00:39.039 --> 00:40.123
[Arlong] <i>From now on,</i>

00:42.208 --> 00:43.626
<i>you belong to me.</i>

00:44.544 --> 00:47.297
<i>You draw maps for me.</i>

00:48.298 --> 00:49.883
<i>You have a gift.</i>

00:52.052 --> 00:55.722
<i>And I'm going to use it
to rule these seas.</i>

00:58.433 --> 01:00.560
<i>You'll pay me 100 million Berry.</i>

01:01.811 --> 01:05.106
<i>I don't care how you get it.
Steal it if you have to.</i>

01:09.319 --> 01:10.737
<i>When you're able to pay,</i>

01:11.738 --> 01:13.239
<i>I promise you...</i>

01:16.159 --> 01:18.995
<i>you and your town will have your freedom.</i>

01:25.668 --> 01:29.255
<i>And I always keep my promises.</i>

01:37.222 --> 01:38.473
Arlong did this?

01:40.350 --> 01:41.351
Why?

01:42.936 --> 01:44.354
To punish the villagers.

01:48.817 --> 01:50.068
And to punish me.

01:53.613 --> 01:55.615
[indistinct chatter]

01:56.574 --> 01:58.952
[suspenseful music plays]

02:03.873 --> 02:06.668
- [Nami] What's going on?
- Nojiko told us about your sacrifice.

02:08.586 --> 02:10.964
We didn't know. Can you ever forgive us?

02:10.964 --> 02:12.507
There's nothing to forgive.

02:15.885 --> 02:17.428
Coco Village is my home.

02:17.428 --> 02:21.141
Then it's our turn to sacrifice.
We're done living in fear.

02:21.766 --> 02:25.186
We're gonna march on Arlong Park.
If those fishmen want a fight--

02:25.186 --> 02:28.523
That's not a fight. That's a massacre.
You will all be killed.

02:28.523 --> 02:31.234
[Genzo] If there's no hope
for us to buy our freedom,

02:31.776 --> 02:35.905
then I say we die trying to fight for it!

02:35.905 --> 02:37.615
[villagers yelling]

02:40.118 --> 02:41.619
[Nami] No, everyone, please!

02:42.245 --> 02:44.455
No, I... I won't let you do that.

02:47.500 --> 02:48.793
This is my fight.

02:49.586 --> 02:50.420
[Luffy] No.

02:51.796 --> 02:53.089
This is our fight.

02:53.590 --> 02:54.424
Right, guys?

02:54.424 --> 02:57.510
- Finally, I get to cut something.
- But how are we gonna beat Arlong?

02:57.510 --> 03:00.513
- We saw what he did at Baratie.
- Every creature has a weakness.

03:00.513 --> 03:03.266
- Even bulletproof ones?
- I'll know it when I see it.

03:04.350 --> 03:05.518
And when I do,

03:07.353 --> 03:08.813
I won't hesitate.

03:09.898 --> 03:11.900
[theme music plays]

03:21.326 --> 03:23.286
[seagull squawking]

03:23.286 --> 03:25.371
[indistinct chatter]

03:28.750 --> 03:30.126
[Bogard] Captain Nezumi.

03:32.587 --> 03:34.505
How fares the 16th Branch?

03:34.505 --> 03:36.007
Very well, thank you.

03:36.007 --> 03:39.302
What brings a vessel of your notoriety
to our tranquil shores?

03:39.802 --> 03:41.930
Follow me. Your men can stay behind.

03:53.524 --> 03:54.776
[Bogard] Vice-Admiral.

03:56.778 --> 03:59.364
The welcoming party has arrived.

04:00.198 --> 04:03.409
Vice-Admiral Garp.
What a pleasure to see you.

04:03.409 --> 04:06.788
You might not think it's a pleasure
when you hear what I have to say.

04:07.288 --> 04:10.708
I have received word
of pirate activity at Coco Village.

04:10.708 --> 04:13.711
Yes, an unfortunate incident.

04:13.711 --> 04:16.798
I assure you,
we have the situation under control.

04:16.798 --> 04:19.676
We also have word
that Arlong and his fishmen

04:20.385 --> 04:22.929
have been running wild
across these islands.

04:22.929 --> 04:24.806
We have been tracking Arlong, yes.

04:24.806 --> 04:29.894
But there is a new crew in these parts,
led by a ruthless killer.

04:29.894 --> 04:31.938
A pirate in a straw hat.

04:31.938 --> 04:35.566
He's the one responsible
for this brutal attack.

04:35.566 --> 04:36.693
- What?
- No.

04:36.693 --> 04:38.236
- Cadets.
- That's not possible.

04:38.236 --> 04:40.154
Are you calling me a liar, boy?

04:41.114 --> 04:42.865
Luffy would never do anything like that.

04:42.865 --> 04:47.203
How dare you accuse me?
I am a Marine captain.

04:47.203 --> 04:48.288
I'm a vice-admiral.

04:49.205 --> 04:51.457
So let's move past
the grandstanding, shall we?

04:53.584 --> 04:55.044
My apologies, Vice-Admiral.

04:55.044 --> 04:57.672
I'll make sure these pirates
taste the steel of my blade.

04:57.672 --> 04:59.215
You'll do no such thing.

05:03.845 --> 05:04.721
Where is he now?

05:05.805 --> 05:07.015
Where is Luffy?

05:07.515 --> 05:11.102
Let's pick up the pace!
You know Arlong hates to wait.

05:11.102 --> 05:12.353
[indistinct chatter]

05:13.563 --> 05:15.315
[fishmen clamoring]

05:18.484 --> 05:22.739
What the hell is this? Who would be
stupid enough to attack us?

05:22.739 --> 05:24.824
[suspenseful music plays]

05:28.995 --> 05:31.706
Fishmen! Stand by to repel boarders!

05:38.838 --> 05:40.131
Where's Arlong?

05:40.840 --> 05:42.633
He's probably in the map room.

05:43.718 --> 05:45.178
Then that's where we're going.

05:48.514 --> 05:50.641
[fishmen yell]

05:50.641 --> 05:52.477
[action music plays]

05:58.524 --> 06:00.485
[grunting]

06:16.084 --> 06:17.377
Not the face.

06:17.377 --> 06:18.628
Shit.

06:28.513 --> 06:29.847
What is this place?

06:29.847 --> 06:31.766
Let's just grab our map
and get out of here.

06:37.438 --> 06:39.440
He let me stop wearing them when I was 12.

06:40.566 --> 06:42.151
He said it was a birthday gift.

06:44.904 --> 06:46.656
Come on. Let's go.

06:47.824 --> 06:49.409
[Arlong] But you just got here.

06:49.409 --> 06:50.701
[sinister music plays]

06:50.701 --> 06:52.703
[Arlong laughs]

06:54.622 --> 06:56.666
Welcome to Arlong Park.

07:00.378 --> 07:02.213
[chuckles]

07:02.213 --> 07:04.298
[suspenseful music plays]

07:05.091 --> 07:06.467
[panting]

07:12.598 --> 07:13.641
[growls]

07:16.644 --> 07:17.728
Ah!

07:34.745 --> 07:36.539
[grunting]

07:47.717 --> 07:50.803
- I had that one.
- If you had him, I wouldn't have got him.

07:50.803 --> 07:52.388
[fishmen yelling]

07:59.395 --> 08:03.691
[Arlong] Humans have ruled the seas
for far too long.

08:04.233 --> 08:07.278
Looking down from their ivory towers.

08:07.278 --> 08:10.198
Towers built on the backs of fishmen.

08:10.198 --> 08:13.910
Your government fear my people, so

08:15.369 --> 08:17.622
you forced us into slavery.

08:17.622 --> 08:19.790
No one should be forced into anything.

08:19.790 --> 08:21.667
Everyone should be free
to live as they choose.

08:21.667 --> 08:23.920
[Arlong] Save your sympathies, boy.

08:24.504 --> 08:28.966
Our abuse and persecution end now.

08:30.259 --> 08:34.972
I will lead the fishmen
as we mount a revolution for the ages.

08:34.972 --> 08:38.809
It's your turn
to know humiliation and pain.

08:38.809 --> 08:40.269
Haven't you done enough?

08:40.269 --> 08:43.356
I'm just getting started, darling.

08:44.607 --> 08:48.319
But, Nami, you...
you could have been spared,

08:48.986 --> 08:51.656
taking your place right by my side.

08:51.656 --> 08:55.493
But no, just like the rest of your kind,
you betrayed me.

08:56.369 --> 08:58.162
And for what? For this?

08:58.162 --> 09:00.873
You were never going to spare me.

09:01.541 --> 09:03.459
You told Nezumi about my stash.

09:03.459 --> 09:05.044
[chuckles]

09:05.044 --> 09:07.588
I'm just playing by human rules.
[chuckles]

09:08.589 --> 09:13.844
With these maps, I will create a world
where the fishmen reign supreme.

09:13.844 --> 09:17.390
With knowledge of every Marine base
and pirate stronghold,

09:17.390 --> 09:20.601
nothing can stop me
from taking the East Blue

09:20.601 --> 09:23.020
and every other sea after that.

09:23.521 --> 09:24.438
Oh yes.

09:25.147 --> 09:28.192
And, Nami, it's all thanks to you.

09:30.027 --> 09:31.070
Hmm.

09:32.238 --> 09:36.200
So tell me, Pirate King...

09:37.451 --> 09:38.411
[gasps]

09:39.829 --> 09:42.790
Could you have used her so effectively?

09:43.457 --> 09:45.001
Use?

09:51.591 --> 09:53.384
[grunts]

09:55.261 --> 09:56.137
[grunts]

09:56.137 --> 09:59.640
- No!
- Nami isn't some tool to be used!

10:00.141 --> 10:03.728
She's a person
with wants and dreams of her own,

10:03.728 --> 10:06.063
and you took those away from her.

10:06.063 --> 10:09.400
You're no better than that Axe-Hand guy
or that fake butler

10:09.400 --> 10:12.153
or anyone else
who tries to hurt other people.

10:13.863 --> 10:16.157
So I'm gonna kick your ass,
just like I did theirs.

10:16.782 --> 10:17.992
[chuckles]

10:17.992 --> 10:21.871
'Cause no one messes with my friends.

10:21.871 --> 10:25.458
I'll do you the kindness
of killing you all together.

10:25.458 --> 10:26.792
Get out of here, Nami.

10:26.792 --> 10:28.961
- But, Luffy--
- Just go. I got this.

10:28.961 --> 10:30.796
[Arlong] Think you can escape me, Nami!?

10:32.340 --> 10:34.050
[grumbles]

10:34.842 --> 10:36.636
Round two, Arlong.

10:40.056 --> 10:41.307
[panting]

10:45.436 --> 10:46.312
[grunts]

10:49.690 --> 10:53.152
I just need one clean shot. You got this.

10:53.152 --> 10:54.820
Come out
and face the wrath of my special...

10:54.820 --> 10:56.739
Ah! Ah! [grunts]

10:56.739 --> 10:59.200
[grunting]

11:00.868 --> 11:02.870
[action music plays]

11:04.038 --> 11:05.039
You look tired.

11:07.416 --> 11:09.126
Maybe you should take a break.

11:11.629 --> 11:14.215
- You ought to get back in the kitchen.
- Quit screwing around!

11:15.716 --> 11:16.842
Luffy needs us!

11:19.887 --> 11:22.014
You just got here.
You don't know what Luffy needs.

11:22.765 --> 11:26.686
- I know he needs my cooking.
- Putting two slices of bread together?

11:30.272 --> 11:32.692
- [Buggy] Someone's feeling threatened.
- [both] Shut up!

11:32.692 --> 11:36.404
[Buggy] Then get me back to my body!
We're close. I can feel my toes.

11:36.404 --> 11:38.531
Trust me.
I can help you guys win this thing.

11:38.531 --> 11:40.408
I swear, clown, if you screw us over...

11:41.992 --> 11:43.494
Ow! God!

11:45.538 --> 11:46.372
Yes!

11:52.670 --> 11:54.880
Yes! Yes! Oh!

11:54.880 --> 11:58.134
Oh, it's so much better
than I even remembered.

11:59.802 --> 12:01.595
Hey, so, um...

12:02.680 --> 12:04.098
I'm gonna get out of here.

12:05.057 --> 12:07.059
- Hey!
- [Buggy] Sorry, kiddos.

12:07.059 --> 12:10.771
I'd love to make things right,
but it's time to exit stage left.

12:11.981 --> 12:13.023
Fucking clown.

12:15.693 --> 12:17.236
[suspenseful music plays]

12:20.364 --> 12:21.323
[whispers indistinctly]

12:32.710 --> 12:36.714
Too bad, little one. Just when
we were starting to have some fun.

12:41.510 --> 12:43.512
[playful music plays]

12:45.639 --> 12:46.515
[Usopp] Gotcha.

12:46.515 --> 12:49.560
Hey, neck flaps, where are you going?

12:50.352 --> 12:52.271
You haven't even tried my hot sauce.

12:53.689 --> 12:55.316
[fishman] That still won't save you.

12:55.983 --> 12:58.068
My skin is tougher than bullets.

12:58.569 --> 13:02.364
Maybe you should try
one of my new patented fire rounds.

13:02.364 --> 13:03.616
I'm a fishman.

13:04.325 --> 13:05.701
I don't catch fire.

13:05.701 --> 13:07.036
Maybe you don't.

13:11.165 --> 13:12.291
But alcohol does.

13:14.251 --> 13:16.170
Special Attack. Exploding Star!

13:22.343 --> 13:23.844
Yeah! Ha!

13:23.844 --> 13:28.516
Take that! The Great Captain Usopp
fells another notorious villain.

13:28.516 --> 13:30.184
[laughs]

13:30.184 --> 13:34.980
And no one's around to see it.

13:36.649 --> 13:37.691
It's okay.

13:38.734 --> 13:39.693
They'll believe me.

13:40.903 --> 13:43.405
How dare you strike down my brothers?

13:45.366 --> 13:48.869
You won't be so lucky
against the might of my fishman karate.

13:48.869 --> 13:50.955
[action music plays]

13:53.833 --> 13:56.418
- [grunts]
- [grunts]

14:00.673 --> 14:02.049
[grunts]

14:02.591 --> 14:03.717
[both grunting]

14:07.429 --> 14:10.307
[Luffy grunting]

14:11.767 --> 14:12.810
[Luffy grunts]

14:12.810 --> 14:13.769
[Arlong growls]

14:14.562 --> 14:15.396
[grunts]

14:17.815 --> 14:18.899
Get up.

14:20.651 --> 14:25.364
Even with your Devil Fruit powers,
you're no match for me, boy.

14:25.364 --> 14:28.784
Maybe so, but you made our navigator cry.

14:28.784 --> 14:30.661
Gum Gum Pistol!

14:31.370 --> 14:32.329
Ah!

14:36.792 --> 14:37.835
[laughs]

14:37.835 --> 14:38.961
Yes!

14:40.546 --> 14:41.630
[Arlong laughs]

14:42.756 --> 14:44.633
[yells]

14:44.633 --> 14:46.719
[laughing]

14:46.719 --> 14:49.096
[cracking]

14:51.640 --> 14:53.392
[grunting]

14:57.730 --> 14:59.565
[grunts]

15:05.696 --> 15:06.530
[groans]

15:06.530 --> 15:10.367
You're no match for me.
My kicks can break a ship's keel.

15:10.367 --> 15:13.078
That's nothing.
You should have seen Zeff's kicks

15:13.078 --> 15:15.539
when he found an eggshell
in the crème brûlée.

15:15.539 --> 15:17.833
I get it. Zeff was mean to you. Boo-hoo.

15:18.667 --> 15:19.543
[yells]

15:25.925 --> 15:26.842
[grunts]

15:26.842 --> 15:31.639
You're nothing but a fool
if you think you can save Nami.

15:31.639 --> 15:32.848
[chuckles]

15:33.891 --> 15:36.602
There's a reason
she keeps coming back to me.

15:36.602 --> 15:38.646
Arlong Park is her home.

15:38.646 --> 15:40.189
You mean her prison.

15:40.189 --> 15:43.233
[Arlong] Like it or not,
I brought out the best in her.

15:43.233 --> 15:45.611
She'd be nothing without me.

15:46.236 --> 15:47.071
No.

15:51.200 --> 15:53.410
You'd be nothing without her.

15:54.078 --> 15:54.912
[yells]

15:57.122 --> 15:58.165
[Arlong] Typical human.

15:58.165 --> 16:01.085
You can't win
if you can't even hit straight.

16:01.085 --> 16:02.795
Maybe I can't beat you.

16:02.795 --> 16:03.879
[chuckles]

16:03.879 --> 16:09.051
But I can destroy everything you've built.

16:13.847 --> 16:15.182
[yells]

16:16.684 --> 16:17.935
No!

16:19.311 --> 16:21.063
[Arlong yells]

16:21.063 --> 16:22.523
[Luffy] Ah!

16:26.360 --> 16:27.403
[yells]

16:32.366 --> 16:33.367
[Arlong grunts]

16:34.326 --> 16:35.577
[yells]

16:36.578 --> 16:37.830
No!

16:39.081 --> 16:40.416
[Luffy yells]

16:42.167 --> 16:43.419
[grunts]

16:43.419 --> 16:44.503
[yells]

16:46.463 --> 16:48.340
[Luffy yells]

17:01.395 --> 17:05.149
Nami is a fool to have her faith
in such weak compatriots.

17:06.025 --> 17:10.195
You don't ever badmouth Nami.

17:10.195 --> 17:11.655
Now you've done it.

17:11.655 --> 17:12.906
<i>Côtelette!</i>

17:14.199 --> 17:15.034
<i>Collier!</i>

17:15.659 --> 17:16.660
[groans]

17:16.660 --> 17:17.578
<i>Épaule!</i>

17:19.329 --> 17:20.622
<i>Poitrine!</i> [grunts]

17:23.375 --> 17:25.002
[coughs]

17:25.002 --> 17:26.336
<i>Mouton</i> Shot!

17:27.171 --> 17:28.839
[groans]

17:33.385 --> 17:34.970
<i>Mouton</i> shot?

17:34.970 --> 17:37.514
All great fighters call out
their finishing moves.

17:39.850 --> 17:41.310
Yeah, you're gonna fit in just fine.

17:41.310 --> 17:42.561
[yelling]

17:42.561 --> 17:45.355
Never fear, the Great Captain Usopp is...

17:46.231 --> 17:47.232
is...

17:48.358 --> 17:50.652
Oh. You guys did pretty good in here.

17:51.528 --> 17:53.280
[sighs]
Good job, guys.

17:54.198 --> 17:55.449
[sighs]

17:59.787 --> 18:00.871
Nami!

18:02.498 --> 18:03.957
[Nami] You're all okay!

18:06.335 --> 18:07.336
Where's Luffy?

18:09.421 --> 18:10.631
Still inside,

18:11.131 --> 18:12.341
fighting Arlong.

18:13.467 --> 18:14.843
[Usopp] He's gonna be all right.

18:17.471 --> 18:18.514
Right?

18:18.514 --> 18:21.058
[suspenseful music plays]

18:22.935 --> 18:24.520
- [roars]
- [yells]

18:24.520 --> 18:29.149
Gum Gum Gatling!

18:48.961 --> 18:55.592
No puny human can bring down Arlong Park!

18:57.010 --> 18:58.011
[yells]

18:59.429 --> 19:01.723
Gum Gum...

19:04.017 --> 19:06.061
- [grunts]
- ...Battle Axe!

19:06.061 --> 19:08.522
[yells]

19:08.522 --> 19:10.440
[Along screams]

19:18.574 --> 19:19.449
Luffy!

19:43.765 --> 19:45.809
[somber music plays]

20:07.748 --> 20:10.292
[uplifting music plays]

20:21.637 --> 20:22.471
[Luffy] Nami!

20:23.513 --> 20:25.015
You are our friend!

20:26.016 --> 20:27.517
We are your crew!

20:28.268 --> 20:29.645
[Sanji laughs]

20:35.234 --> 20:36.485
[Usopp laughs]

20:39.529 --> 20:41.907
[all laughing]

20:49.498 --> 20:51.500
[upbeat music plays]

20:58.548 --> 21:00.259
[overlapping chatter]

21:03.679 --> 21:04.554
[Sanji] Bon appétit.

21:04.554 --> 21:06.765
- Thank you.
- No worries. Have a good night.

21:06.765 --> 21:09.559
- Hey!
- I'm gonna need these recipes too.

21:09.559 --> 21:11.895
- [Sanji chuckles]
- [Nojiko] You should write a cookbook.

21:11.895 --> 21:14.898
Well, you know, a true artist
never reveals his secrets,

21:14.898 --> 21:18.819
but I could be talked
into offering some private lessons.

21:20.946 --> 21:22.489
- Nice try.
- [chuckles]

21:23.991 --> 21:25.659
[Sanji] There you go, my lovely. Enjoy.

21:26.410 --> 21:27.327
Ooh.

21:27.327 --> 21:29.663
Back for seconds. Must have liked it.

21:29.663 --> 21:32.332
- Yeah, it was okay.
- That plate says different.

21:32.332 --> 21:35.294
Gotta keep my strength up,
even with your cooking.

21:35.294 --> 21:39.006
It's the least you can do, considering
I saved your ass from those fishmen.

21:39.006 --> 21:42.217
- What? I saved <i>your</i> arse.
- You didn't even get your hands dirty.

21:42.217 --> 21:44.636
At least I don't need three swords
to prove I'm a man.

21:48.140 --> 21:49.224
There I was,

21:50.267 --> 21:52.644
completely alone,

21:53.270 --> 21:55.314
surrounded by fishmen,

21:56.148 --> 22:01.528
the Great Captain Usopp
staring death in the face.

22:02.821 --> 22:05.365
But I knew I couldn't give up the fight,

22:06.199 --> 22:09.202
not with the fate
of Coco Village at stake!

22:09.202 --> 22:11.913
So I pulled my trusty slingshot!

22:12.748 --> 22:14.207
[mimics sound of shot]

22:14.207 --> 22:15.417
[mimics explosion]

22:16.168 --> 22:19.129
And I fired on 'em till my fingers bled.

22:19.629 --> 22:25.260
And I didn't stop until I single-handedly
defeated Arlong and his deadly crew.

22:27.846 --> 22:30.307
With a little help, of course.

22:30.307 --> 22:31.641
I mean,

22:31.641 --> 22:35.562
I guess I wasn't completely alone.

22:36.396 --> 22:40.192
Three cheers for Captain Usopp!
We couldn't have done it without him!

22:40.192 --> 22:41.568
Whoo!

22:41.568 --> 22:43.862
[villagers cheering]

22:48.408 --> 22:49.868
[man] Marines!

22:50.452 --> 22:51.536
Form lines!

22:51.536 --> 22:53.622
[military march music plays]

22:59.503 --> 23:01.296
I'd rethink that if I were you.

23:02.506 --> 23:05.217
[Garp] So these are the Straw Hat Pirates.

23:06.385 --> 23:07.219
Huh.

23:08.553 --> 23:09.429
Marines,

23:10.222 --> 23:11.306
arrest them.

23:11.306 --> 23:14.935
Sir, the Straw Hats didn't destroy
Coco Village. It was Arlong.

23:17.604 --> 23:19.147
You have your orders, cadet.

23:20.899 --> 23:21.733
No.

23:26.613 --> 23:28.990
- What did you say?
- I said no, sir.

23:28.990 --> 23:34.204
You do realize there are severe
punishments for disobeying direct orders?

23:35.414 --> 23:36.998
I disagree with those orders, sir.

23:37.582 --> 23:38.792
[Garp scoffs]

23:39.960 --> 23:40.794
Me too.

23:41.837 --> 23:42.671
[sighs]

23:43.547 --> 23:44.423
Huh.

23:45.090 --> 23:47.342
Anyone else like to follow their lead?

23:48.176 --> 23:50.846
Or do you all want
to follow orders instead?

23:55.308 --> 23:57.060
Any of them move,

23:57.644 --> 23:59.229
make sure it's their last.

23:59.229 --> 24:01.231
Come here, boy.

24:09.197 --> 24:13.994
I gave you every opportunity
to follow my path,

24:13.994 --> 24:16.246
to become a respected Marine.

24:18.039 --> 24:19.207
But instead,

24:20.750 --> 24:22.586
you chose to become a pirate.

24:24.921 --> 24:25.964
No, Grandpa.

24:27.841 --> 24:29.843
I've always been a pirate.

24:29.843 --> 24:31.178
[Garp] No more running, boy.

24:31.178 --> 24:32.387
Last chance.

24:32.971 --> 24:33.805
Give it up.

24:34.514 --> 24:36.141
That's not really my thing.

24:38.727 --> 24:40.395
[suspenseful music plays]

24:42.481 --> 24:44.274
Then show me what you've got.

24:45.400 --> 24:46.318
[yells]

24:59.873 --> 25:01.833
[Garp] This is what you wanted, right?

25:01.833 --> 25:03.335
To be a pirate.

25:04.211 --> 25:06.922
Well, I'll show you
what Marines do to pirates.

25:07.422 --> 25:11.176
- I don't want to fight you, Grandpa.
- You've been fighting me your entire life.

25:16.056 --> 25:17.015
[Luffy] Ah!

25:18.642 --> 25:20.936
When are you gonna learn
that you can't win?

25:22.687 --> 25:24.064
[coughs]

25:24.064 --> 25:25.815
[groans]

25:39.955 --> 25:41.957
I thought I trained you better than this.

25:44.000 --> 25:45.335
You did.

25:49.047 --> 25:50.966
[grunts]

25:53.009 --> 25:55.637
Gum Gum

25:56.304 --> 25:59.683
Rocket!

25:59.683 --> 26:00.850
Ah!

26:12.362 --> 26:14.781
You don't know how dangerous the world is.

26:17.909 --> 26:20.787
The Grand Line isn't some child's game.

26:21.663 --> 26:23.164
[grunts]

26:23.748 --> 26:26.626
I told you, you aren't ready.

26:27.127 --> 26:29.796
You can hit me all day long...

26:31.798 --> 26:34.259
but I'm never giving up on my dream.

26:35.385 --> 26:38.471
- Is that so?
- I'm going to the Grand Line.

26:39.556 --> 26:41.474
And I will find the One Piece.

26:44.603 --> 26:45.687
And I will be...

26:47.731 --> 26:49.065
King of the Pirates.

26:54.988 --> 26:56.114
[chuckles]

26:58.074 --> 27:01.411
[laughing]

27:03.788 --> 27:04.748
[Luffy grunts]

27:09.502 --> 27:10.503
[chuckles]

27:12.339 --> 27:14.341
[laughing]

27:16.009 --> 27:18.428
[uplifting music plays]

27:23.141 --> 27:24.184
[sighs]

27:26.811 --> 27:27.979
Have it your way.

27:29.689 --> 27:30.732
Lower your weapons!

27:33.777 --> 27:35.862
What are you all standing around for?

27:35.862 --> 27:38.239
Arlong's pirates are still on the loose.

27:38.740 --> 27:40.325
Hunt them down and arrest them.

27:47.707 --> 27:49.209
What about these Straw Hats?

27:49.209 --> 27:50.377
What about them?

27:50.377 --> 27:52.712
Arrest them too!
They are the real criminals.

27:52.712 --> 27:53.630
[grunts]

27:54.964 --> 27:55.924
Ooh.

28:06.935 --> 28:09.729
I knew I'd never be able
to change your mind.

28:09.729 --> 28:11.356
You're stubborn.

28:12.649 --> 28:13.566
Just like me.

28:14.859 --> 28:16.945
But I know who you are, boy.

28:19.280 --> 28:21.866
I just needed to make sure
you knew it too.

28:24.994 --> 28:26.246
You were testing me?

28:29.165 --> 28:31.000
Couldn't you have gone
a little bit easier?

28:31.960 --> 28:33.378
Where's the fun in that?

28:41.511 --> 28:42.762
You're on your own now.

28:50.061 --> 28:52.522
No. I'm not.

28:55.233 --> 28:56.317
I have my friends.

28:56.818 --> 28:58.820
[emotional music plays]

29:11.875 --> 29:12.792
[Nami] I did it, Mom.

29:17.130 --> 29:18.047
I'm free.

29:22.135 --> 29:24.262
My life is finally my own again.

29:27.849 --> 29:30.351
I can move forward with my head held high.

29:32.896 --> 29:34.606
That's what you always wanted, right?

29:44.407 --> 29:47.744
I'm sorry I didn't understand
the sacrifices you made for me.

29:52.207 --> 29:53.082
But now I do.

29:56.628 --> 29:59.756
I know what it means
to fight for your family.

30:02.383 --> 30:04.761
And I promise
I will never lose sight of that.

30:10.809 --> 30:11.810
I know it's late, but I...

30:16.314 --> 30:17.982
I hope you'd be proud of me.

30:17.982 --> 30:19.818
[sentimental music plays]

30:20.777 --> 30:22.570
[Nojiko] She was always proud of you.

30:26.241 --> 30:27.116
And so am I.

30:30.829 --> 30:31.746
How's your arm?

30:36.417 --> 30:38.670
A little sore, but...

30:41.047 --> 30:41.923
worth it.

30:46.177 --> 30:47.011
Thank you.

30:48.680 --> 30:53.184
Oof, no. Um, those words still sound
a little weird coming out of your mouth.

30:53.184 --> 30:54.352
[both laugh]

30:55.019 --> 30:57.355
- Unnatural, right?
- [Nojiko] Just a little.

30:59.357 --> 31:00.859
Do you really have to leave?

31:01.943 --> 31:04.237
I was just starting to like you again.

31:07.448 --> 31:09.033
As nice as that is...

31:12.996 --> 31:13.955
I do need to go.

31:14.789 --> 31:15.832
[Nojiko] I know.

31:16.457 --> 31:18.293
I just want you to remember that

31:19.335 --> 31:20.920
no matter how far you go,

31:22.046 --> 31:24.507
you will always have
a place here to return to.

31:25.466 --> 31:28.469
- This will always be your home.
- Mm-hmm.

